.SH SHCrossPowerL
Compute the cross\-power of two real functions for a single spherical
harmonic degree.
.SH Usage
\f[CR]cpower\f[R] = SHCrossPowerL (\f[CR]cilm1\f[R], \f[CR]cilm2\f[R],
\f[CR]l\f[R])
.SH Parameters
.TP
\f[CR]cpower\f[R] : output, real(dp)
The cross power of the two functions for spherical harmonic degree
\f[CR]l\f[R].
.TP
\f[CR]cilm1\f[R] : input, real(dp), dimension (2, \f[CR]lmaxin1\f[R]+1, \f[CR]lmaxin1\f[R]+1)
The spherical harmonic coefficients of the first function.
.TP
\f[CR]cilm2\f[R] : input, real(dp), dimension (2, \f[CR]lmaxin2\f[R]+1, \f[CR]lmaxin2\f[R]+1)
The spherical harmonic coefficients of the second function.
.TP
\f[CR]l\f[R] : input, integer(int32)
The spherical harmonic degree.
This must be less than or equal to the minimum of \f[CR]lmaxin1\f[R] and
\f[CR]lmaxin2\f[R].
.SH Description
\f[CR]SHCrossPowerL\f[R] will calculate the cross\-power of two
functions expressed in 4\-pi normalized spherical harmonics for a single
spherical harmonic degree \f[CR]l\f[R].
This is explicitly calculated as:
.PP
\f[CR]cpower = Sum_{i=1}\(ha2 Sum_{m=0}\(hal cilm1(i, l+1, m+1) * cilm2(i, l+1, m+1)\f[R].
